In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry all produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into 1/2-inch-thick
wedges; mince one wedge until you have 1 TBSP. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1} into
1/2-inch pieces. Mince @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Pat @Diced Steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels.

> For 4 servings, mince a few onion wedges until you have 2 TBSP.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, and juice from half the lime; season with salt.

Add @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoon} to a separate small bowl. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches
a drizzling consistency.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and onion wedges.
Season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred, ~{7-9%minutes}. Transfer veggies to a
plate.

> For 4 servings, use a large pan.

Add another drizzle of oil to same pan; increase heat to high. Add steak and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring
occasionally, for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex Paste{1} and @water{1/4%cup} until combined. Bring to a simmer and cook until mixture is saucy and steak
is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}, lime zest, and half the cilantro. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with veggies, saucy steak, salsa, crema, remaining cilantro, and any remaining sauce
from pan. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.